According to reports, the hair is from a young Jewish girl was killed in Auschwitz concentration camp. Girls at this camp were shaved before they were sent to the gas chambers. The 78-year-old toy was believed to have been typically gifted to the children of rich German families and high-ranking Nazi officers. The doll is currently on display at the Anatolian Toy Museum in Turkey. Auschwitz exhibit to open in NYC An extensive exhibit on Auschwitz, the Nazi concentration camp, will open next week in New York and includes 700 Holocaust artifacts, most never before seen in the United States. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by
